# Separate Files, Clear Responsibilities

- Prefer one primary responsibility per file.
- Keep UI orchestration in window/page code-behind; move non-UI logic to dedicated services/helpers.
- Use partial classes only to organize a single type by feature area, not to hide unrelated responsibilities.
- Extract reusable logic into separate classes when methods are pure or broadly reusable.
- Move nested data models to dedicated files when they are used outside a tiny local scope.
- Keep file names descriptive and aligned with responsibility (for example, `RenameExecutionService`).

## Practical guidance

- If a file grows large because it mixes loading, navigation, mutation, and persistence, split by those concerns.
- Preserve behavior first during refactors, then improve abstractions in follow-up changes.
- Prefer small, composable services over adding more stateful methods to UI classes.
